comments.body:
@nalind Thanks for rapid response. You are right. `COPY pnpm-lock.yaml /app` results in creation of a file `/app`.  
I have tried your suggestions in the beginning and none of them worked unfortunately.

I have played today with the build process and found that **an** answer to this issue, was to first do `WORKDIR /app` and only then start copying stuff into it. But of-course, it is not going to be a solution for everyone.
